.TH "s3c2410_calc_bank" 9 "s3c2410_calc_bank" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
s3c2410_calc_bank \- calculate bank timing information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" s3c2410_calc_bank
.BI "(struct s3c_cpufreq_config *cfg "  ","
.BI "struct s3c2410_iobank_timing *bt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cfg" 12
The configuration we need to calculate for.
.IP "bt" 12
The bank timing information.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Given the cycle timine for a bank \fIbt\fP, calculate the new BANKCON
setting for the \fIcfg\fP timing. This updates the timing information
ready for the cpu frequency change.
